caption: Our favorite romantic spot!  Love the food, and Antonio the owner and his staff are friendly wonderful people.
The food is delicious and staff are so friendly! When my takeout order was missing an entree they promptly got it to me along with an extra free entree. Great food, value, and service!
The ravioli con pera e pecorino as well as the pannacota for desert were absolutely delicious!  We got take-out of course but it all tasted fantastic.  Thank you!
Awesome. Best lasagna ever. Everybody was so nice. I will be back
Simple tasty filling Italian cuisine. Local fav
Very yummy Italian food — loved the seafood pasta and burrata!! Great service, covid friendly, warm, and they even treated us to limoncello! Tiramisu  amazing
Very good authentic Italian! Cozy, nice atmosphere, polite staff. Look forward to returning.

Their cocktails were strong and the deserts were tasty. Though our pasta was under cooked and the table we sat at was slanted enough for our drinks and plates to slide a few inches whenever we set our silverware down. Granted this is their outdoor seating, so they get props for having it at all. Long wine list and friendly wait staff!
Very fresh pasta and great service.

Napoli pasta bar is always a treat there’s always something exciting and new on the menu there’s so many nice regional dishes that remind me of Naples Italy and new dishes that are very well thought out and delicious. We particularly like the pasta with corn and crab. The drinks are also excellent and the owner and his wife could not be more committed to you’re having an enjoyable evening. This is really just a great place to go for a really enjoyable dinner with family your friends

Delicious dinner, one of the best cooked chickens I have ever had and the pannacotta dessert was a perfect finish. Really nice ambiance and cute decor. Staff were all great, checked on us a few times, especially Giulia she was amazing and helped us choose the best drinks for our meal.
One of the best chef in DC!
Wonderful patio that is dog friendly. Service, drinks, and food were great!

DISCLAIMER: This is my first indoor dining experience pre-Covid 19.  I've driven past this spot on many occasions and finally decided to stop in. The paint and accompanying murals make it easy to spot especially since they sit in an area lined with row houses. It was very hot outside and we were lucky enough to call them and get seating within 15 minutes.  Coming in, the spot has a great old world energy and a good layout. There is an antique register at the bar and authentic plates from Naples decorated on the wall. There is also a coffee bar at the other end of the restaurant which looked enticing. The dining area was split off per social distancing guidelines and we were seated close to the bar. The staff was friendly and were gracious hosts. I felt well attended. The menu was small but that is a hopeful sign that the dishes that are offered are well done and thought out.  We ordered drinks, appetizer, two dishes and dessert. Drinks were both very tasty, I had a bourbon drink with bitters, my girlfriend had a summery drink with aperol. Appetizer was the eggplant parmesan along with complimentary bread and olive oil. Tasty. My girlfriend especially enjoyed it. Main dish was an Old Bay pasta with crab meat and braised beef with pasta. All of the food was very good, fresh, and made to order. My girlfriend doesn't like lemon and the old bay pasta was very zesty so we ended up switching plates. I liked it. The braised beef was great as it was not too saucey and the beef managed to stay juicy. Not sure what exact cut the beef was but I know it has a tendency to be stringy and dry. Not the case here. Both dishes had perfectly cooked al dente pasta. For dessert I had the tiramisu with an espresso and she had the flourless chocolate cake with a scoop honey and fig gelato. Both were great and I especially loved the tiramisu. It was rich while not being too wet which made it memorable to me.  Overall, the experience was positive. I enjoyed being out of the house talking to people that were easy to talk to, expressed passion in their restaurant, and took steps to make us feel welcome. I would recommend Napoli Pasta Bar to my friends for an authentic Neapolitan dining experience that does not involve pizza.
Great take out options (pre-fix menu) during COVID shutdown. Fast friendly service. Lots of food that makes very yummy leftovers

Got an amazing cocktail, appetizer, salad, two entrees, two deserts FEAST to go for my husband and me, and omg they did their jobs well. Fresh pasta, great drinks, quick service, and completely on the social distancing guidelines. We will be going back.  Thanks Napoli crew!
Love it!
Andy Clark has done amazing things to this little neighborhood Italian spot.  Take a walk outside of the normal and go here for a date night or just for a good meal

We live right down the street from Napoli and stop by often for happy hour/dinner. Great happy hour specials, but worth it even without happy hour prices. Service is attentive and the bartender and owners are very friendly, always up for a chat. The outdoor patio is great on a non-humid day The pasta is delicious, the perfect comfort food.
Really great food, wonderful vibes, and friendly service. I highly recommend it!
Fabulous local restaurant serving great pasta. Better than most places in DC. You won't be disappointed.
Great pasta and food.

Tasting Squid, Burrata, Carpaccio, and Truffle is required  (Original) Me parece un sitio especial , con una excelente comida y un especial Limonchelo. Authentic Italian restaurant where food is made with love!

Overall wonderful experience. The burrata was wonderful. The Tagliolini was exceptional - pasta itself was a wonderful texture and the preparation was perfectly balanced.  The gnocchi was light and delicious, with a truly unique fennel flavor unlike anything I've had before.  Highly recommended.
Unremarkable.

Napoli is a very cute little Italian restaurant, but their row house charm is pretty much the best of our restaurant experience tonight. I could have excused the poor service if the food was better, and I could have excused the mediocre food if the service was better.  It was an average Friday crowd and they still had DC restaurant week menu options available. The laggy service exacerbated by only having the one server carrying plates up and down stairs. Bussing the the tables was just as awkward with all kinds of clumsy reaching and elbows. To top it off, there was no attempt to refill drinks, even when someone specifically asked for another glass of wine, everyone else was sitting with empty glasses.  Specific disappointing food options include the caprese salad, marinara sauce, and tiramisu.
Delicious HH specials! Definitely coming back for dinner soon

Was soo excited to try the tiramisu. Not good at all! Didn’t seem like they made it in the restaurant (or it at least seemed like it had been sitting there for days). The drinks were great and the pasta was fresh.

Every time I visit Napoli, I am more and more impressed, with the food, the atmosphere, but perhaps most of all with the service - the perfect mix of warmth & welcome, yet always professional. It may be just a bit off the beaten track, but ignore that and go see for yourself. It's so good you will want to move into the neighborhood.

Staff very friendly and authentic.   Decor very cozy and inviting. Fresh Italian bread with olive oil a very nice touch. We are late at 9:00 and ordered the caprese salad and a meat ravioli dish recommended by proprietor.   We shard both dishes as food is pricey, most items in the teens and portions are not big, However , everything is made from scratch and you do not feel stuffed after eating, more satisfied. The caprese salad was excellent with fresh tomatoes, mozeralla and basil and seasoned appropriately. The ravioli meat dish was ok, the red sauce tasted a bit overcooked, but it was late in the dinner hour. I think plain ravioli with a side of sauce would have been a better choice. The restaurant should simplify their menu, although authentic to Italy, I think they would attract more of the locals. And lower prices.   Our bill was $39 before tip fir two dishes.  Also, no kids menu. Or they could go more family style with larger plates of food. If money is no object, it’s worth the experience.

The restaurant lives up to its name and Michelin Bib Gourmand star - authentic and just as good as the restaurants in Naples and Amalfi from our honeymoon! Not a morsel of food was spared.  t's pretty cozy so get here early or make a reservation. We got there right at 4:30pm opening time and luckily could do a walk-in as the restaurant was all booked up!  My hubby enjoyed the Brigante aged rum cocktail so much he got around round! The bartender had a heavy poor the 2nd time around.  The complementary Rosemary Focaccia bread served with first-press olive oil was divine. The bread was so soft and fluffy with a thick crust on top, we definitely got a refill!  The Melanzane de Eggplant was scrumptious with fresh smoked mozzarella, ricotta cheese, San Marzano tomato, and layers of eggplant. It's worth saving room for the appetizer. Highly recommend it!  The Tagliatelle al Porcini with black truffle ($8 upcharge - totally worth it!) was scrumptious. The long noodles were cooked al-dente in a olive oil, parmesan cheese, and garlic sauce. The porcini mushrooms complemented the noodles and elevated the flavor. While the black mushrooms were a nice add-on, the dish was good enough to stand on its own.  My hubby got the Fish of the Day, which the server kindly debone. There were a few small pieces of bone, so just be careful. He thoroughly enjoyed the well-cooked fish which was elevated with sweet cherry tomatoes soaking up the juices. We couldn't remember the unusual name of the dish, it wasn't catchy, but similar to a Cod. The side of sauteed spinach was tasty and paired well.  While we were stuffed and failed to save room for dessert, the decadent Tiramisu was well worth it! The layers of moist lady fingers sandwiched in mascarpone cheese with rich chocolate chips and topped with expresso was heavenly!  This homey restaurant is truly a hidden gem in Columbia Heights and 5 stars in my book! Excited to come back and will make a reservation!

Ate here a second time and I didn't find it very remarkable. The service is really great with everyone from the person who greets you to the runners taking good care of the diners. But the food was lack luster. Many of the pasta dishes were lacking salt and pepper. The fish of the day was cooled perfectly but didn't have much else with it. The food was what left is disappointed. The decor and the art design on the interiors are really cool. Just needs tastier food.

OMG!!! we had a great great time, the Neapolitans Owner and Chefs where so warm, we had the BACCALA FRITTO (Fresh cod fish fritters) with fresh tomatoes, kalamata olives, capers sauce. Delizioso!!! Second Dish, cooked to perfection al dente Pasta with slow cooked meat and San Marzano tomato sauce. Delizioso!!! I Cafesito, Perfect!!! At the end a nice picture with Diego Maradona Mural, great touch. Thanks a lot.
Amazing and Authentic place
Beautiful space and I had high expectations but the food was very disappointing. We got two appetizers and two pasta dishes but only ate half. Two stars instead of one since the service was good.

Underwhelming food, nice atmosphere and service. As others have stated, the portion size is very small. Flavor-wise most dishes were lacking as well. From all I tasted, I’d recommend the gnocchi most. It’s simple but prepared well.  My veal dish (rolled with ricotta and raisins) was terrible, something clearly went wrong. The staff very kindly put in an order for me of something else and comped my entrée entirely.

It was ok. I wouldn't go back. Service was acceptable. The portions small, but the food was good. I appreciate the restaurant being in the neighborhood and it's style, but the price and service aren't there for me. The two others I was with felt the same way. We don't regret going but we wouldn't be back.
Neighborhood restaurant, gave it a second try. Great atmosphere and mediocre food!
Was okay expensive pasta chill atmosphere
Nice atmosphere and service, food was mediocre at best.
A gem in Washington DC. 100% Italian (from Naples), 100% delicious, 100% friendly service. I would recommend it to my best friends.  Just go and enjoy it! :)

(Translated by Google) The food is fine, but don't order take away. I have never had such small portions for so much money! Absolutely grotesque expensive.  (Original) Maden er fin, men lad være at bestille take away. Jeg har aldrig fået så små portioner til så mange penge! Helt grotesk dyrt.
Absolutely amazing meal. Great service and finished off our wonderful trip to Washington D.C.
Really nice place.
Amazing food with a great neighborhood friendly atmosphere. The service was above  expectations always having a full glass. Highly recommended!
Love this place! Great neighborhood restaurant with excellent Italian food and good service

Good staff recommendations for appies and mains. While decent portions if you were a larger eater you would not be satisfied.  I found both appie and meal slightly bland, my partner however thought them a good balance of flavours and textures.

Antonio was awesome - we had an amazing time. Veggie friendly. Burrata was fresh from Italy which is amazing for the price point of this place. Will definitely be back soon!! Outdoor seating with white tables was a nice touch.
(Translated by Google) Excellent and delicious dishes  (Original) Excelente y los platillos deliciosos
Great food...great service...would definitely go back again.
Amazing pasta and a cozy vibe
Gluten-Free options, just ask.  Delicious food with a European atmosphere.  Wine was less than amazing, but overall, a worthwhile experience, would visit again.
Faultless. Seven of us dived deep in the menu, from cocktails through dessert. Envious that NY nephew has this gem in his neighborhood.
This place has a very good vibe, the outdoor area is specially nice and the food is great!
The customer service is excelent, the food depending on how much you like italian tradituonal food can be very good.
The staff were kind and attentive. The food was not good. The pastas were thick and chewy. The flavors were bland and under salted (I never add salt to my food). Am surprised at the Michelin rating.
I went for the lasagna brunch. I liked it.  and the buns are incredible too.  (I'm a gourmand) I think the service could have been a bit better, but I liked it
Good, simple food overall. I thought it was a bit overpriced.
Always amazing home made Italian dishes that make you want to book a flight to Italy. The owner Antonio, is always friendly and welcoming.
Best servise and food ever! For the first time in DC my dinner was not ruined and it was honestly Great.

Food was excellent. I had a winter veggie lasagna that I would highly recommend.  Only thing to keep in mind is this is a smaller dining room. You'll want a reservation, but even with one you may have to wait for a table to become available. If you're flexible, you can find a seat at the bar and order food from there.
Very intimate and service was great. Portion size small, but seasoned well. Not enough meat options on their Restaurant Week Menu.
Excellent service and food!
The drink menu is amazing and so is the eggplant appetizer!

We went here for restaurant week and the food was amazing. I got the spaghetti with octopus and shrimp and it was very good. I got a beef based appetizer which was delightful. I also got two glasses of good wine with the restaurant week deal. The staff were very friendly and we had quick service. The bread was to die for.
Solid southern Italian fare for those who know what Baccalà Is.  Worth the trip
Excellent food and great service

The menu was not large but ample selection for varying tastes. The food was very tasty, thoughtfully prepared and well presented. Even the bread was a delicious fresh focaccia. Excellent service. The prices were reasonable considering the quality. Will return and would recommend.

Some of the best pasta I've had in a long time. The rigatoni was excellent. Sat at the bar and the old fashioned was also very good. They played the college football playoff, which is very difficult to find at a place with food this good.

Amazing taste and nice atmosphere in our local neighborhood. True Italian feel in a very not Italian city. The owner offered to debone our fish and did a great job. We had a mushroom tomato eggplant bruschetta to start with and then we shared the oven baken cod and finished with tiramisu and panna cotta. It was amazing! The prices aren’t cheap but hey, where can tou eat like in Italy in this town and pay nothing for it? Exactly. Wish they got rid of the tacky TV that is so standard in every American restaurant...
Good pasta. A bit too noisy
Really buzzing and high energy on Saturday night- great, flexible service and great appetizers, especially the cod and burrata
Don't miss the desserts - sleeper hits
A plesant neighborhood Italian restaurant.

I oredered the Genovese for pick-up. At $20 I expected a larger serving particularly since it didn't taste that great. The dish is described as including slow cooked meat. My bowl contained 2 small cubes that were far from tender. If you're portions are this small it should be made up by exceptional flavor. I do not recommend Napoli Pasta Bar.

This is a really small and cute restaurant on Sherman, with good food and reasonably priced wine.  They had just gotten their Michelin Bib Gourmand award and the place was jammed and the staff were having a hard time keeping up.  I'm sure this place will hopefully calm down a bit because it's a terrific neighborhood place.
Great food! Great service! Genuinely Italian.

Great to have this place in the neighborhood. The food and service are excellent. I saw a few reviews complaining about portion size and price but can't agree they should impact the rating. Yes, the portions aren't huge like you're at the Cheesecake Factory but you'll certainly be full. The prices are a bit premium (maybe a dollar or two more per item). However, the owner and staff clearly put a lot of effort into making the place friendly and welcoming. They also try to create a sense of community that is sorely lacking in this area; greeting passers by and remembering their customers by name. Napoli can gladly have my extra $5 and keep the extra 2 bites of food every day of the week in exchange for bringing those qualities to the neighborhood. They run a place neighbors want to go to and are happy to have in the community.
Best pasta in DC and amazing wines. Desserts are killer too. Owner Antonio is a super nice guy!
Great pasta bar, good value for money and fantastic service. Will definitely be back.
I was reluctant to recommend this place only because I'm concerned it will get too popular. Heroic jem of a restaurant. Get the 10-hour rigatoni.
Wonderful food in a welcoming setting.
Solid Italian food. Lively atmosphere. Friendly safe.
Great service and tasty pasta. Try the Paccheri Ragu and the Gnocchi.
Good southern Italian food. Great atmosphere and staff. Felt like being back in Italiy. Highly recommended.
The food was cooked perfectly.  Waiters were attentive and very nice.  Atmostphere was wonderful... not much more you could ask in a resturaunt.
Amazing food, a little on the pricey side. Seems authentic.
Food was fantastic, one of the best places for Italian in DC. Service was great too. Reasonably priced as well. Highly recommend
Great authentic Neopolitain food and excellent service. Going back again soon!

It was nice.  Portions are small compared to most places but I think it was sized right however the price of those small portions could be cheaper.  Unfortunately my pasta arrived a little too al dente for me (so much so that it was difficult to cut with a knife).  Our waiter offered to send it back but I declined and let my partner have it instead.  Otherwise it was a very pleasant visit.

Place is awesome, met the owner hes extremely cool. Havnt had the food yet but the bar scene is great. Good beers on tap and the Sambuca extra chilled with 3 espresso beans is a great way to end the week!! Highly recommend!!

We went as part of a large group and had an awesome meal. Will definitely go back. As a vegetarian had great options. The eggplant appetizer was shared by several of us and we actually exclaimed “wow” in surprise when we each had a bite on how good it was.  I had the gnocchi which was awesome and my wife had a gluten free pasta with vegetables fish which she loved. The cannoli dessert was also a favorite among our group. Fun setting and vibe as well. Really good.
Nice reasonable portions of excellent pasta at reasonable prices. Great new neighborhood place!

I went here with a couple of friends Friday evening. It had rained and so everyone from the patio moved into the restaurant. We made a reservation and was about 30 mins late, but we were seated within 5-10 mins! So definitely make a reservation if you have a party of 4 or more. The ambiance was awesome and the food to pair was amazing! The cod and octopus entree is to die for! The canoli desert was delicious. The owner, Antonio, came by several times to our table to make sure everything was going well, which to me makes a big statement. My friends and I had a great experience there and we will definitely be coming back. Thanks Napoli Pasta Bar- you will now be my go-to for authentic Italian food!
Great food and service
Very unique atmosphere and awesome food!
Simply great Italian place!!!
Delish and reasonably priced wine

The food is very overpriced for unfortunately small portions. The food was tasty enough, but my noodles we're a bit undercooked and my friend's gnocchi a bit dry. The staff is very friendly, and service was excellent. I would go for a nice date, but other than that, avoid it. Too high a cost for what it is.
Everything is very tasty but pasta portions and wine pours are too small, especially for the price. Seriously, if the food and wine portions were just a fraction larger, it would be perfect

Enjoyed our dinner at Napoli tonight! We visited the amalfi coast last year, and the food at Napoli is both authentic and delicious. The owner is from Positano, and he and the staff are passionate about the food as well as making sure each customer enjoys their meal. Highly recommended!
Food is delicious but a bit salty for my taste.
A big upgrade from the last restaurant that was here. Cocktails were quite good (and only $10), as was the food. I wouldn't say anything blew me away, but everything was tasty.
Great atmosphere, friendly staff, and good food. What more do you need? Great new addition to the neighborhood eats.
Good food, great wine, friendly and pleasant atmosphere!
What a treat to have in the neighborhood! Great food and amazing pasta. The atmosphere was very authentic and the service was excellent!
